  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shelter NFIs Response to Conflict Affected IDPs in Fenti/Zone 4 of Afar, Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Identification/selection, verification and validation of eligible beneficiaries in IDP sites in Haridor, Dibina, Walae, Menafesha locations. Purchase and transportation of consigned NFI kits to target woreda.  Market assessment will be conducted. The project will purchase 3000 bed sheets, 3000 bed mats, 1500 mosquito nets, 1500 kettles (aluminum), 3000 plates, 6000 caps, 1500 cooking pots, and 1500 ladles, 1500 washing basin, 1500 jerry canes, 1500 multipurpose liquid soap, 1500 handwashing jug and basin set and 4500 soaps.
Distribution of NFI (bedding set, kitchen set and hygiene set) to 1,500 eligible households. 
Establish hand washing points and provision of COVID19 protection gears mask, gloves, and hand sanitizers for distribution team.
Post distribution monitoring</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved living conditions of displaced and conflict affected 1,500 households or 8,250 people supported with core relief items (shelter NFIs) - These NFIs help the affected community to be saved and protected from physical and/or environmental challenges and for preparing their food. Bedding set: blankets, bed matters and mosquito nets protect them from harsh weather conditions: cold, and from malaria. Other NFIs help the affected community for proper preparation and healthy handling and serving of food stuff to their family and eventually contributed towards improved the living conditions of the displaced and conflict affected households.</narrative>
  </description>
